> Chris,
>
> I wouldn't be messing around with those "paper tubes" with my
> bare hands if I were you - I did it myself 'till I read somewhere that
> those were made of asbestos - and that material, as you know is
> prone to cause cancer. At the time the buses were assembled it
> was the best heat isolating material around and it's downside
> wasn't yet on the public view. Use a mask too if you're working
> directly under the bus.
>
> I hope I'm not being too paranoid here!
> Greets to all you guys!
>
